    <item>
      <title>特朗普回归为以色列提供了破坏伊朗核计划的机会</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/trump-s-return-gives-israel-a-gap-to-derail-iran-s-nuclear-plans</link>
      <description><![CDATA[以色列认为唐纳德·特朗普在美国大选中的戏剧性胜利使其可以放手继续对哈马斯和真主党发动战争，甚至考虑实施旨在摧毁伊朗核计划的打击。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/trump-s-return-gives-israel-a-gap-to-derail-iran-s-nuclear-plans</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 17:01:01 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>内塔尼亚胡解雇以色列国防部长加兰特引来愤怒和赞扬</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/israel-pm-netanyahu-s-sacking-of-defense-chief-yoav-gallant-draws-ire-and-praise</link>
      <description><![CDATA[以色列总理本雅明内塔尼亚胡周二晚间突然解雇了国防部长，此举不仅免除了内阁批评者的职务，也加深了反对者对他处理该国多线冲突方式的愤怒。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/israel-pm-netanyahu-s-sacking-of-defense-chief-yoav-gallant-draws-ire-and-praise</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 14:36:44 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>投资者如何应对特朗普的胜利</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/wall-street-reacts-it-s-full-risk-on-as-trump-scores-win</link>
      <description><![CDATA[周三，随着唐纳德·特朗普 (Donald Trump) 赢得美国总统第二任期，在与副总统卡马拉·哈里斯 (Kamala Harris) 的势均力敌的角逐中，冒险狂潮席卷金融资产。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/wall-street-reacts-it-s-full-risk-on-as-trump-scores-win</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 14:12:14 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>共和党接近三连胜，民主党赢得美国众议院的希望逐渐渺茫</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/us-house-is-democrats-best-hope-in-brutal-election-for-party</link>
      <description><![CDATA[民主党通过控制美国众议院对唐纳德·特朗普进行强有力制衡的希望正在逐渐消退，而共和党则越来越有信心，他们将在明年围绕减税和支出的大战之前在华盛顿保持统一控制。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-06/us-house-is-democrats-best-hope-in-brutal-election-for-party</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 06 Nov 2024 08:43:32 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
